  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 2160 mg
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/lemon-tortelloni-palermo-with-shrimp-649339c04b18c31a619ff77b
cuisine: Italian
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @bell pepper{1}; remove stem and seeds. Place on a #baking sheet{}; drizzle each half with @olive oil{2%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Arrange cut sides down.

Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While bell pepper roasts, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water. Pat shrimp dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1.5%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}.

Add tomato; cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @pesto{4%tbsp}, and @water{1/3%cup}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook until sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

> Use pan used for shrimp here.

Once water is boiling, add @cheese tortelloni{9%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and floating to the top, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Transfer roasted bell pepper to a #cutting board{}; thinly slice.

Heat pan with sauce over medium-low heat. Stir in drained tortelloni, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} (save the rest for serving), and as much lemon zest and lemon juice as you like. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until cheese melts and pasta is coated, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in bell pepper. If needed, stir in reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until tortelloni is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide tortelloni between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with scallion greens and remaining Parmesan. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Top tortelloni with shrimp.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.